transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hey, thanks for calling Viagra. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, hi. I'm calling because I don't want to be on that automatic refill program.

Speaker 1: I never signed up for that.

Speaker 2: What was your last name?

Speaker 1: I'll spell it. D-I-P-P-O-L-I-T-O.

Speaker 2: And your zip code?

Speaker 1: 08094.

Speaker 2: Bruce?

Speaker 1: Correct.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, I can stop that for you, Bruce. Not a problem at all.

Speaker 1: Looks like you got set up on our VIP prescription there.

Speaker 2: And I wanted to offer you, before I did cancel,

Speaker 1: let you know I can pause these refills as far as six months in advance.

Speaker 2: That way you can always call us in between if you did want to get a refill order or anything like that,

Speaker 1: or online you can do that as well.

Speaker 2: I just wanted to offer you that before I did cancel it outright.

Speaker 1: We are the only FDA-approved company with the medicine.

Speaker 2: If I do cancel, I wouldn't be able to open it back up for you.

Speaker 1: So I just wanted to make sure you were aware before I stopped that for you completely.

Speaker 2: Well, so I would be put on pause for six months and then automatically be put back on it?

Speaker 1: Not automatically, but if we didn't hear from you, yeah, it would start back up.

Speaker 2: But if you called us, like, any time before as well, you don't have to get a refill.

Speaker 1: You just say, hey, you know, I need a little more time, or I'm traveling, or I just don't need them now,

Speaker 2: or I need them sooner, and it's all, you know.

Speaker 1: Okay, let's cancel it.

Speaker 2: One more time? Sorry, I didn't hear you there.

Speaker 1: I just canceled it.

Speaker 2: Okay, no worries. I'm going to cancel that for you, Bruce.

Speaker 1: Like I said, we won't be able to sell you anymore in the future,

Speaker 2: and we are the only company with those pills from Pfizer, okay?

Speaker 1: Okay, thanks.

Speaker 2: I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: We'll be back in about a month.

Speaker 2: I'll probably be back in about a month.

Speaker 1: Thank you so much.

Speaker 2: No worries.

Speaker 1: No worries.

Speaker 2: So you're all set there, okay?

Speaker 1: You're good to go.

Speaker 2: Thank you, Bruce.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
